Donald Trump said on Friday Russia should be attending the meeting as he prepared to fly to Canada to attend part of the three-day conference. MOSCOW - Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov, on US President Donald Trump’s remark that Russia should be attending a Group of Seven (G7) nations meeting, said: “Russia is focused on other formats, apart from the G7,” Sputnik reported. Trump said on Friday Russia should be attending the meeting as he prepared to fly to Canada to attend part of the three-day conference. Other leaders of the G7 are set to clash with Trump when they pressure him to lift sanctions on steel and aluminium they fear could lead to a trade war. Trump is scheduled to leave early on Saturday for Singapore to prepare for a summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un on Tuesday.